<p><b>Karl Ernst Ludwig Marx Planck</b>, better known as <b>Max Planck</b><sup id="cite_ref-marx_1-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-marx-1" title=""><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup> (April 23, 1858 – October 4, 1947) was a <a href="/wiki/Germany" title="Germany">German</a> <a href="/wiki/Physicist" title="Physicist">physicist</a>. He is considered to be the founder of the <a href="/wiki/Quantum_mechanics" title="Quantum mechanics">quantum theory</a>, and one of the most important physicists of the twentieth century.</p>
